Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm
wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the bowl and toss in the
pickling liquid. Set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}(grated).
Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(thinly sliced).

When the wedges have been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, heat a #large frying pan{}
on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and
fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon to break it up as it cooks, then
drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the mince has browned, add the garlic to the pan and fry for ~{1%minute}.
Stir in the @gochujang paste{50%g}, @water{75%ml} and half the @hoisin sauce{64%g}.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your #bowls{}. Spoon over the
gochujang beef, then top with the cheese and pickled slaw. Drizzle the
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and remaining hoisin sauce on top. Sprinkle with the sliced
spring onion and @black sesame seeds{5%g} to finish. Enjoy!